o apply the patch I posted in my previous email to the kernel list. If it<br />_still_ locks up, I need to know. <br /><br />Talking about needing to know - if anybody is interested in a pre-2.0.32<br />that has the Pentium lockup fix, I just made pre-patch-2.0.32-3 available<br />on ftp.kernel.org.  NOTE NOTE NOTE!!!! This is just a back-port of the<br />2.1.x version, and I have not tested it myself due to my lack of Pentiums<br />to test with. It does compile, but that's all I can say.. <br /><br />		Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
